cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image reconstruction using prior knowledge in the form of training images. This is a common problem in computer vision and image processing, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a non-negative dictionary and regularization techniques also suggests that the paper may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the algorithm to non-overlapping patches of the image suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
